    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>To work on your exercises and your project, you will need the following software.</p>\n<h2 id=\"java\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#java\" aria-label=\"java permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Java</h2>\n<p>We will use <a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/news/announcement/oracle-releases-java-17-2021-09-14/\">Java 17</a> in this course, the latest long-term support release of the language.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://blog.saverioriotto.it/files/uploads/news/medium/9501631890607.jpg\" alt=\"java17\"></p>\n<p>You don't have it installed yet, now is the time!</p>\n<h2 id=\"ide-integrated-development-environment\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ide-integrated-development-environment\" aria-label=\"ide integrated development environment permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IDE: Integrated development environment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.techgalery.com/2019/12/java-ide-options-for-beginner-and-pro.html\"><img src=\"https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-bDkr24hyJzU/XfrgSUB5dFI/AAAAAAAAFow/k7OY-A7tDckOlQ7bfANETW29ue7jl6z9wCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/java-ides.jpg\" alt=\"IDEs\"></a></p>\n<p>We will NOT force you to use a particular IDE in this course.</p>\n<p>Instead, I would like you to:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Try out different IDEs</li>\n<li>Choose your favorite one</li>\n<li>Tell me why! I'll ask some of you about it in our next class</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Here are some popular options:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/\">IntelliJ IDEA</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">Visual Studio Code</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/release/kepler/sr1/eclipse-ide-java-developers\">Eclipse</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://netbeans.apache.org/\">NetBeans</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can find many reviews and comparisons online, such as:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.infoworld.com/article/3114167/choosing-your-java-ide.html\">Choosing your Java IDE: Compare Eclipse, NetBeans, and IntelliJ IDEA for features, usability, and project size and type</a><br>\nBy Martin Heller at InfoWorld</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.javacodegeeks.com/2019/11/visual-studio-code-vs-intellij-idea-which-is-best-for-java-devs.html\">Visual Studio Code vs IntelliJ IDEA â€“ Which is best for Java devs?</a><br>\nBy Illana Brudo at Java Code Geeks</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.techgalery.com/2019/12/java-ide-options-for-beginner-and-pro.html\">Java IDE Options For Beginner And Pro Java Programmers</a><br>\nBy Adam Mudianto at Techgalery.com</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You are free to choose the IDE you enjoy coding on the most!</p>\n<p>We will use Maven to install dependencies, build, package, and run your assignments and projects, so there is no need to worry about your IDE choice.</p>\n<h2 id=\"git\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#git\" aria-label=\"git permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Git</h2>\n<p>In this course, we will use <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/\">Git</a>, a free and open source distributed version control system.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Git-logo.svg/1280px-Git-logo.svg.png\" class=\"gatsby-img-attributes\" style=\"width: 300px;\" alt=\"git\" title=\"\"/></p>","frontmatter":{"slug":"/introduction/tools","title":"Tools","course":"Programming Project 2021/22","previous":"/introduction/bibliography","next":"/introduction/evaluation","chapter":1,"section":6,"module":"Introduction"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/introduction/tools"}},
